cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation of crop fields using CNNs, which is a classic computer vision problem falling under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed system is designed to operate on a real agricultural robot, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of existing vegetation indexes, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The system is trained using a comparably small amount of training data, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of real-time operation in the fields, which involves the use of sensors and data processing techniques, falling under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
